title: MotoGP Malaysian Grand Prix 2015: Where to watch qualifying live and practice review
text:
October 23, 2015 20:14 BST Jorge Lorenzo was the fastest during FP2 of the 2015 Malaysian Grand Prix Getty 
Yamaha rider Jorge Lorenzo was the fastest during the second practice session 2015 Malaysian MotoGP Grand Prix on Friday. 
Where to Watch Live 
The third practice session starts at 2.55am BST . Live coverage of the qualifying for the Australian Grand Prix starts at 7.10am BST on BT Sport 2 and BT Sport 2 HD. Real-time internet updates are available on MotoGP's official website. 
Practice Review 
Lorenzo was the second fastest in Free Practice 1, behind Dani Pedrosa as the Honda rider was the fastest with a time of 2:00.412s. However, Yamaha rider bounced back in the second session on Friday as he clocked a time of 2:00.246s and ended the day on the top. 
Pedrosa was the second fastest in Free Practice 2, ahead of his Honda teammate and defending champion Marc Marquez. The defending champion clocked a time of 2:00.472s and finished in third spot. 
Ducati rider Andrea Iannone was fourth, while Britain star and LCR's Cal Crutchlow was fifth with a time of 2:01.039s. Yamaha rider Valentino Rossi managed to finish in top 10 as he finished in eight place. 
Top 10 qualifying result from Sepang International Circuit: 
1. Jorge Lorenzo (ESP) Yamaha 2:00.246s 
2. Dani Pedrosa (ESP) Honda 2:00.293s 
3. Marc Marquez (ESP) Honda 2:00.472s 
4. Andrea Iannone (ITA) Ducati 2:00.486s 
5. Cal Crutchlow (GBR) LCR 2:01.039s 
6. Aleix Espargaro (ESP) Suzuki 2:01.058s 
7. Andrea Dovizioso (ITA) Ducati 2:01.127s 
8. Valentino Rossi (ITA) Yamaha 2:01.305s 
9. Danilo Petrucci (ITA) Pramac 2:01.598s 
10. Scott Redding (GBR) Estrella 2:01.607s
